::Savanna::

She thought to herself, For a pride of bots, they sure don't act like 
a pride.

She ran off into the grass lands to hunt.  She found a small herd of 
Zebra and layed low in the grass.  She stealthily crept closer and 
closer to on Zebra which was standing a little ways away fron her.  
She crept in closer and closer.  POUNCE! She ran after the creature 
with speed and accuracy.  She jumped and bit down on it's neck and 
pulled it to the ground.  She dragged the zebra back to the base and 
ate heartliy.  

After a bit, she sat under a small shade tree and relaxed in the 
day's heat.  She felt like her old self again.  She looked at what 
was left of the carcass.  It had reminded her of old kills with her 
pride back home.  But here she was, with a bunch of bots she didn't 
really know. She felt a little like an outcast.  She layed her head 
down on her paws.  She realy missed her pride.
